e operating system kovacs previewed firefox os at mobile world congress  garnering commitments from  major worldwide mobile operators in  kovacs negotiated a reported  billion deal renewing mozilla’s agreement to make google the default search engine in firefox kovacs also steered mozilla to a position as industry leader in internet privacy initiatives most notably firefox now offers collusion an addon that enables users to view all third parties tracking their online activity and in turn to make more informed decisions about being tracked the ponemon institute named mozilla the “most trusted internet company for privacy” for  kovacs is a frequent public speaker and panel member his  ted talk tracking the trackers explores issues of internet privacy in an increasingly connected world at the world economic forum annual meeting of the new champions in  he presented on strategies for creating a resilient cyber economy amid economic security and privacy obstacles he was a keynote speaker at the mobile world congress  fierce wireless named kovacs one of the rising stars in wireless for  on april  mozilla announced that he would step down as ceo of the corporation later that year and until march  he was part of mozillas board of directors on july   kovacs joined avg technologies as ceo in september  avg technologies was acquired by avast software  kovacs was terminated  from avg technologies in december  personal lifeedit raised by hungarian parents in toronto kovacs began experimenting with technology at a young age though grateful for the opportunities and education provided by his native canada his interest in innovation drew him to the san francisco bay area he now lives in piedmont california referencesedit  a b van wageningen ellen  january  web’s impact ‘mindboggling’ leadership forum told the windsor star kovacs    httpswwwtedcomspeakersgarykovacs  missing or empty title help  alec scott lessons from canadas silicon valley diaspora” the globe and mail published  f